# 🧪 Lab 3 – Registry (30 Minutes)

## Open Registry Editor

Run:

```text
regedit
```

---

Navigate to:

```text
HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services
```

Observe:

Every Windows Service has its own Registry key.

---

Find these services:

* Spooler
* BITS
* wuauserv (Windows Update)
* RemoteRegistry

Observe:

* ImagePath
* DisplayName
* Start
* Type
* DependOnService

---

## Registry Values

### ImagePath

Shows executable location.

Example:

```text
C:\Windows\System32\spoolsv.exe
```

---

### Start Value

| Value | Meaning   |
| ----: | --------- |
|     0 | Boot      |
|     1 | System    |
|     2 | Automatic |
|     3 | Manual    |
|     4 | Disabled  |

---

### Type

Represents the service type (kernel driver, file system driver, Win32 service, etc.).

---

## Export Registry Key

Right-click:

```text
Spooler
```

Choose:

```text
Export
```

Save as:

```text
Spooler.reg
```

---

## Restore Registry

Double-click:

```text
Spooler.reg
```

or

```cmd
reg import Spooler.reg
```

---

## PowerShell

List services Registry keys

```powershell
Get-ChildItem HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services
```

Read one service

```powershell
Get-ItemProperty HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Spooler
```

